We recommend the Management to:
Direct the Municipal Budget Office to prepare the Registry of Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations (RAOO) for QRF, MOOE, and CO;
Require the Municipal accountant to prepare Subsidiary Ledgers (SLs) for Trust Liabilities-DRRMF account pursuant to Section 5.1.12 of COA Circular No. 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012, specifically for transfers of agency’s unutilized DRRMF to the special trust fund by year of transfer;
Ensure that at the end of each year, the Municipal Accountant transfers all the unexpended/unobligated balance of the QRF and the DRRMF - MOOE to the Special Trust Fund under the account “Trust Liability - DRRM”;
Accordingly, make the necessary journal entries to transfer the unexpended QRF and DRRMF-MOOE to the special trust account for 2024; and
Direct the Local DRRMO to submit a copy of the LDRRMFIP for prior years duly approved by the Municipal Mayor.

Compel all the Special Disbursing Officers concerned, to submit immediately the necessary documents and cashbooks/records to fully account and liquidate their long overdue cash advances and instruct the Accountant to monitor closely the liquidation of these cash advances in accordance with the reglementary periods prescribed under Section 1.2 of COA Circular No. 2012-001;
Require all concerned SDOs to returned immediately all unspent cash advances, and in case of non-compliance, instruct the Accountant and the Treasurer to deduct and withhold from the salaries and allowances of the concerned SDOs, an amount to satisfy or settle their unliquidated advances; and
If warranted, initiate the filing of appropriate administrative charge against the concerned SDOs for their failure to render their accounts under Sections 89 and 128 of PD No. 1445 and Article 218 of the Revised Penal Code.

Instruct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to submit the lacking 40 DVs to this Office and the DVs, Payrolls, official receipts and journal vouchers for the period covering from September to December 2023;

Direct the Municipal Treasurer and the Disbursing Officer not to allow other persons to have possession of the DVs and supporting documents and to strictly follow the procedures in the disbursements by check prescribed under Section 44, Volume 1 of MNGAS for LGUs to ensure that copies of the DVs and supporting documents are kept, filed and submitted to this Office completely and on time; and 

Failure on the part of the officials concerned to submit the documents and reports mentioned herein shall automatically cause the suspension of payment of their salaries until they shall have complied with the requirements of the Commission as provided under Section 122 of PD No. 1445.

Provide legal basis why the procurement be considered regular despite the above-cited deficiencies; 

Verify the truthfulness of the Lease Agreement.

Also, ensure that field office’s accessories, communication equipment and IT equipment covered by the contract cost and which met the specification are turned-over to the Local Government Unit of Villanueva upon completion of the project and acknowledged by the LGU end-user thru Property Acknowledgment Receipt. To ensure that the items are new, request for sales invoice.

Require the Accountant and the person having authority over Special Education Fund to charge only allowable expenses to the Fund;
Require the Bid and Awards Committee and the Procurement Unit to follow rules and regulations affecting procurement; and
Expend government funds for necessary expenses.

